text: IV liga Warmia-Masuria group (grupa warmińsko-mazurska) is one of the groups of IV liga, the 5th level of Polish football league system. The league was created in season 2000–2001 after introducing new administrative division of Poland. Until the end of the 2007/08http://www.90minut.pl/archsezon.php?id_sezon=71 season IV liga was placed at 4th tier of league system but this was changed with the formation of the Ekstraklasa as the top level league in Poland. The clubs from Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship compete in this group. The winner of the league is promoted to III liga group I. The bottom teams are relegated to the groups of Liga okręgowa from Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship.
